problem.markdown:
>> Which analogy between optimization and mountaineering is false? <<

( ) Parameter to coordinate {{This is a true analogy. For each set of parameters (coordinates), there is an associated loss value (altitude).}}
(x) Loss to slope {{The loss is analogous to the altitude, whereas the gradient is analogous to the slope. }}
( ) Update to displacement {{This is a true analogy. By updating the parameter values (displacement), the value of the loss function (the altitude) might change.}}
